{"questionId":"22168008","questionHtml":"<p>In the case where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Π</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> is perpendicular to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Π</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> lies on <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Π</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>. Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> and the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>equating their scalar product of the direction normals to zero&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to substitute <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>p</mi></math> and coordinates of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> into <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Π</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22168008","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ2.11b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"In the case where p=-6, Π2 is perpendicular to Π1 and A lies on Π2. Find the value of k and the value of q.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.13—Scalar (dot) product","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.14—Vector equation of line","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.17—Vector equations of a plane","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.18—Intersections of lines & planes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}